commit.message: Bugfix for namedexpr and unicode decoding in annotate_test

Support for async/await syntax + python 3.7/3.8 tests

Bugfix for determining indentation level of unformatted nodes

Explicit tests for PEP 515; numbers with underscores

Support YieldFrom node (python3.3+)

+ add tests for Yield
Move out-of-place comment

Support keywords in ClassDef

Fixes #79.

Updating version to 0.1.8

+ add `six` to `install_requires` in setup.

Support mixing tabs and spaces in indentation level in python2 (#71)

* Support mixing tabs and spaces in indentation level in python2

Fixes #70.

* Rework the indent diffing algorithm to compute widths

A much more sensible approach, given inspiration from @ssbr.

* Fix tests to run on py2 only

commit.message:
Bugfix for indented statements in try blocks

+ an error in ExceptHandler which was masked by this.

Fixes #78.

Treat `Yield` node as an expression, as it is

Fixes #76.

Undefined name 'v' in pasta/base/codegen.py (#74)

* Undefined name 'v' in pasta/base/codegen.py

[flake8](http://flake8.pycqa.org) testing of https://github.com/google/pasta on Python 3.7.1

$ __flake8 . --count --select=E9,F63,F7,F82 --show-source --statistics__
```
./pasta/base/codegen.py:75:23: F821 undefined name 'v'
        if isinstance(v, ast.Str):
                      ^
./pasta/base/codegen.py:76:24: F821 undefined name 'v'
          parts.append(v.s)
                       ^
2     F821 undefined name 'v'
2
```

* Undefined name: v --> val
Bugfix for indent detection
Add RemoveDuplicatesTest to suite (bugfix)

Add python 2/3 trove classifiers (#72)

Clearly identify this project as supporting python 2 and 3.
This is useful for utility programs like [caniusepython3](https://github.com/brettcannon/caniusepython3#how-do-you-tell-if-a-project-has-been-ported-to-python-3).

Update README.md (#69)

Update readme, since fstrings and python3.6 is supported

Detect the indentation used in a module to use for unformatted blocks

Fixes #68.

Bugfix for setting indentation level on child nodes without formatting data

Fixes #62

This previously worked by chance by carrying on the "indent diff" (the
amount that a node is indented relative to its container) onto a block's
children if the children are missing formatting info. However, if the
container is at the top level, it doesn't have any indentation to pass
on. It should be inferring this diff from a child node instead.
Add a function for removing duplicate imports to import_utils
Adding MatMult (@) support (#67)

Updating version to 0.1.7

PEP 448 dict unpacking support + bugfix for fstring parsing

Bugfix for fstring FormattedValues that begin with a paren

The '(' was being incorrectly attributed to the FormattedValue node
rather than its value. FormattedValue nodes don't have extra parentheses
beyond the expression they contain.

Support PEP 448 unpacking

Fixes #64.

Updating version to 0.1.6

Bugfix for python3 kwonlyargs.
